approve(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-approve}. NOTE: If `value` is the maximum `uint256`, the allowance is not updated on `transferFrom`. This is semantically equivalent to an infinite approval. Requirements: - `spender` cannot be the zero address.

cancelBid(uint256).details: This function can only be called by the bidder who submitted the bid.      It ensures the bid is removed from the auction and any locked funds are refunded.

params.bidId: The unique identifier of the bid to be canceled.

claimAllocation(uint256).details: This function is called to transfer the allocated ERC20 tokens to the bidder based on the resolved auction.      It can only be called for bids with an allocation already defined.

params.bidId: The ID of the bid for which the allocation is being claimed.

claimETHToken().details: This function is called by the owner to claimed the ETH won.

confirmBid(uint256).details: The function validates the bid, ensuring the user transfers the necessary ETH associated       to the total value requested to confirm his bid.      The user must call this function after submitting a bid to finalize their participation.      This function must be available only when we have successfuly decypher the total amount       of the user bid (requestedAmount * pricePerUnit)

params.bidId: The unique identifier of the bid to be confirmed associated to the user.

decimals().details: Returns the number of decimals used to get its user representation. For example, if `decimals` equals `2`, a balance of `505` tokens should be displayed to a user as `5.05` (`505 / 10 ** 2`). Tokens usually opt for a value of 18, imitating the relationship between Ether and Wei. This is the default value returned by this function, unless it's overridden. NOTE: This information is only used for _display_ purposes: it in no way affects any of the arithmetic of the contract, including {IERC20-balanceOf} and {IERC20-transfer}.

definedAllocation(uint256).details: This function is called after all bids have been processed and organized based on the best price.      It determines for all the bids the token allocation based on the auction settlement price.      The allocation process may be executed iteratively to handle large data sets without exceeding gas limits.

params.numberToProceed: The number of bids to process in this call.

name().details: Returns the name of the token.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

refundBids(uint256).details: If the users has an allocation, he should claimed it first before getting refund.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

resolveAuction(uint256).details: This function is called after the auction has ended. It processes a specified      number of bids per call to prevent running out of gas in case of a large number      of bids to proceed.

params.numberToProcceed: The maximum number of bids to process in this call.

submitEncryptedBid(bytes32,bytes32,bytes.details: We allow the contract to request future decryption of the encrypted parameters.      At this phase, only the total value amount derived from the input bid will be decrypted.

params.ePricePerUnit: Encrypted price per unit the bidder is willing to pay.
params.eRequestedAmount: Encrypted amount of tokens the bidder wishes to purchase.
params.inputProof: Cryptographic proof verifying the validity of the encrypted inputs.

returns._0: bidId A unique identifier for the submitted bid.

symbol().details: Returns the symbol of the token, usually a shorter version of the name.

transfer(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transfer}. Requirements: - `to` cannot be the zero address. - the caller must have a balance of at least `value`.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transferFrom}. Skips emitting an {Approval} event indicating an allowance update. This is not required by the ERC. See {xref-ERC20-_approve-address-address-uint256-bool-}[_approve]. NOTE: Does not update the allowance if the current allowance is the maximum `uint256`. Requirements: - `from` and `to` cannot be the zero address. - `from` must have a balance of at least `value`. - the caller must have allowance for ``from``'s tokens of at least `value`.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

params.user: The address of the user whose bids are to be fetched.

returns._0: An array of bid IDs representing the bids placed by the specified user.

auctionAllocation().notice: Total number of tokens to be distributed to the bidders.         In case insufficient bidders, the auction is canceled.

auctionSettlePrice().notice: Auction settlement price defined after the resolution phase if sufficient bids.

cancelBid(uint256).notice: Cancels a submitted bid, allowing the user to withdraw their locked funds.

claimAllocation(uint256).notice: Allows a user to claim the allocated tokens for a successful bid.

claimETHToken().notice: Distribute the ETH from the sell auction. The amount is computed based on the settlement price         defined when resolving the auction.

confirmBid(uint256).notice: Confirms a submitted bid by locking the required ETH into the smart contract.

definedAllocation(uint256).notice: Allocates the number of tokens to successful bidders after the confidential bids are resolved.

endAuctionTime().notice: The timestamp at which the auction ends

ethClaimedAfterSell().notice: Indicates whether the owner has claimed the ETH after the auction sale.

gatewayCallbackDecryptBid(uint256,uint25.notice: Gateway Callback - decrypt the bid parameter

gatewaydecryptBidTotalValue(uint256,uint.notice: Gateway Callback - Decrypt the total value of the bid requested

lastBidProcessed().notice: The last processed bid ID (used for managing bid resolution)

nextBidId().notice: The ID of the most recent bid

resolveAuction(uint256).notice: Resolves the auction by processing and decrypting bids in steps.

submitEncryptedBid(bytes32,bytes32,bytes.notice: Submits an encrypted bid for the running auction.

userBids(address).notice: Returns the list of bid IDs placed by a specific user.
